LOL I played several other classes at a good levels before, most notably warrior, rogue and necro at higher levels. The necro was what got me playing the enchanter because I used ST a lot and wanted the full deal with crowd control. Just because I don't post as  them (as they are not active characters atm) doesn't mean I only played an enchanter. Why does it matter how a mage solos or can't get groups? That's a different issue and is not relevant to what enchanters can do. This is about how enchanter charm is 'overpowered' remember?<br>
<br>
Anyways I'm beating a dead horse. Some mages unfortunatly will not be happy until either they get huge upgrades or have everyone else nerfed, and will believe that skills from some classes are overpowered without taking in account everything about the skill. Enchanters obviously won't win a debate on this issue on a magician board. Believe what you will about charm. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4356">Turonyen - Level 60 Enchanter</a><br>
