To those flaming encs:<br>
<br>
I'll say it right out. Charm is the most powerful ability in game. Hell, have a mob use fd to give a mob two weaps, then i dictate and another hits it with VoG as spell lands, I can do around 600 dps if i get the right mob. then I have 48 GURANTEED seconds of that.<br>
<br>
Do a little math, thats nearly 30k dmg. <br>
<br>
Of course, then charm breaks. Now, we have a highly enraged mob kicking my ass. Im dead before I can do jack @#%$.<br>
<br>
So you see, charm is very powerful. BUT YOU FRICKING DIE 99% OF THE TIME IF ONE LITTLE THING GOES WRONG!<br>
And if you don't haste or quad it, then you lose efficiency. its all RvR. The thing with ye mages is your pets never turn on you. Ours do...they do so quite often in fact. Thats why we have more powerful mobs.<br>
<br>
But really, as someone said earlier, its not the ability thats broken. Its the fact that mobs can hit for so damn hard to balance player level. A chanter charming a Guk mob compared to an OS mob, theres a huge difference in power. Theres the real issue.<br>
